A Chelsea player has been included in the UEFA Champions League team of this week. UEFA released the Champions League team in a post via their website on Thursday following the conclusion of this week’s quarter-final second-leg matches on Wednesday night. The Chelsea player included in the Champions League team is Jorginho. Jorginho made the list alongside Real Madrid’s Nacho and Man City stars, Riyad Mahrez and Phil Foden. Recall that Chelsea eliminated Porto, while Real Madrid knocked Liverpool out of the competition and Man City defeated Dortmund. Below is the UEFA Champions League team after the conclusion of this week’s quarter-final second-leg games: Goalkeeper:
Alisson Becker (Liverpool) Defenders:
Nacho (Real Madrid) Chancel Mbemba (Porto) Jérôme Boateng (Bayern) Lucas Hernández (Bayern) David Alaba (Bayern) Midfielders:
Riyad Mahrez (Man City) Jude Bellingham (Dortmund) Jorginho (Chelsea) Phil Foden (Man City) Forwards:
Eric Maxim Choupo-Moting (Bayern)